1.title: Another Way to Fly/A View to a Ball
1.plot: Oso helps a girl how to throw a ball so she can play catch with her brother.

2.title: Dr. Go/For Your Bed Only
2.plot: Oso helps a girl learn how to race her brother's remote-control toy car.

3.title: From China with Love/Thunderbasket
3.plot: Oso and Rick learn how to use chopsticks for Chinese New Year's Eve dinner. / Together, Oso and Pete learn how to shoot a basketball.

4.plot: Oso helps Harper learn how to ride her brand new scooter. / With Oso's aid, Ivan learns how to pick out a picture he wants to colour, choose the crayons, and colour a beautiful picture to show his Dad.

5.title: Goldputter/Live and Leaf Rub
5.plot: Oso swings in to help Ryan and Jayden learn how to play mini golf. / Oso arrives to help Sadie learn how to use white paper and crayons to make a beautiful leaf rubbing to give Grandma.

6.title: Dr. Juice/For Your Nose Only
6.plot: Oso helps Zoe and Alex make orange juice for their mother who is sick; Oso helps Thomas learn to blow his nose.

7.plot: Oso shows up to help Elsa learn how to get acquainted with a dog. / Oso teaches twins Rasheed and Leyla how to play Musical Chairs.

8.plot: Oso comes to the rescue, helping Dylan learn how to make a peanut butter and jelly sandwich before the school bus comes. / Oso helps Sophie finish making carrot muffins for the school bake sale.

9.title: Colors Royale/Cleanfingers
9.plot: Oso comes to the rescue to help Nicholas learn how to mix yellow and blue paint to get green. / Oso helps Charlie learn how to wash his hands before dinner.

11.plot: Oso is excited by the prospect of receiving a special holiday present, but first he has to complete a special assignment. Oso travels all around the globe helping three kids prepare for three different holiday traditions.

12.title: For Angels with Snow/Dr. Snow
12.plot: Oso parachutes in to help Liam learn how to make snow angels in the front yard for his Grandma. / Oso helps Ethan learn the three special steps needed to make a snow globe.

13.plot: Oso helps Henry and Hailey learn how to go sledding before their cousins arrive. / Oso arrives to help Gabriella make paper snowflakes to take to the Winter Festival.

14.title: Dr. Throw/Nobody Plays 'It' Better
14.plot: Oso arrives and helps Rudy learn how to throw a football. / Oso's special assignment is to help Alexander and Elena learn how to play tag.

15.title: Quantum of Sauce/The Girl with the Folded Clothes
15.plot: Oso and Taylor learn how to twirl spaghetti and eat it without spilling a drop of sauce. / Oso helps Lydia surprise her Mom by folding all the clean clothes in the laundry basket.

16.title: Greenfinger/For Sleepy Eyes Only
16.plot: Oso's special assignment is to help Makayla learn how to water plants. / Nadia's too excited about her birthday party tomorrow to go to sleep. Oso helps Nadia learn how to relax and go to sleep.

17.title: Live and Let Heal/GoldenFish
17.plot: Oso helps Malcolm clean a scratch on his knee and cover it with a bandage. / Oso's special assignment is to help Aidan learn how to feed his new pet goldfish Swimmy.

18.title: On Old MacDonald's Special Song/Snapfingers
18.plot: Oso comes to help Spencer and Nicole learn how to snap their fingers. / Henry and Oso learn to play "Old MacDonald" on the piano.

19.plot: Oso arrives and shows Carmen and her cousins how to prepare tamales. / Oso helps Luis and Miguel pick out, fill and hang a piñata for their sister Amelia's quinceañera.

20.title: Lost and Get Found/A View to the Truth
20.plot: When Juan becomes separated from his mother at a department store, Oso shows up to help him. / Lena breaks a vase and lets the dog take the blame. She feels bad and needs Oso to help her learn how to tell the truth.

21.title: License to Order/Table Manners Are Forever
21.plot: Oso arrives and helps Anastasija order her own meal at a restaurant./ Oso helps Zack learn table manners for a fancy dinner.

22.title: A View to a Fire Drill/Thunderbelt
22.plot: Oso arrives and leads Marie and her friends through a practice fire drill. / Oso shows Maya how to buckle her seat belt to go on a drive.

23.title: License to Cheer Up/You Only Vote Once
23.plot: Gavin sees that his friend Jennifer is sad, but doesn't know how to cheer her up. / Julia and her friends can't decide whether to play hopscotch or kickball so Oso helps them learn how to take a vote.

24.plot: Oso helps Audrey learn how to make a healthy snack to take to school. / Oso's special assignment is to help Athena learn how to drink from the water fountain at her school playground.

25.title: Dye Another Egg/Dr. Skip
25.plot: Chiara and Gabriel want to dye eggs for the Easter egg hunt tomorrow, but they don't know how.

26.title: For Your Hands Only/Thunderbeam
26.plot: Oso helps Eun-Kyung make a special handprint as a Mother's Day gift for her Mom. / Together Oso and Leah practice walking across a balance beam.

27.title: Best Friends Are Forever/For School Days Only
27.plot: Madison is sad because her best friend Aaliyah is moving./ Oso arrives and helps Evan get ready for his first day of Kindergarten.

28.title: A View to a Goal/Sweep Another Day
28.plot: Oso jetpacks in and shows Alberto how to kick a soccer goal just like his big brother Marco. / Oso teaches Xavier how to sweep the floor.

29.title: Freeze Dance Royale/The Boy with the Cardboard Fort
29.plot: Oso arrives and helps Mia and Lin learn how to play freeze dance. / Wyatt wants to make a fort out of a big box, but how does he do it?

30.plot: Min wants to surprise her Mom by making her a paper fan to bring to the Cherry Blossom Festival. / Oso arrives and shows Dimitri how to make a connect the dots picture.

31.plot: Chris and Kaitlyn both want to play with a toy cash register, but there's only one toy cash register to play with! / Jordan wants to be polite when he asks for a birthday party goody bag, but he isn't sure how.

32.plot:

33.title: Sock Puppet Royale/Costume of Solace
33.plot: Lauren wants to make a sock puppet so she can participate in a puppet show. / Oso helps Amanda learn how to dress up like a princess.

34.title: Diamonds Are for Baseball/Tomorrow Never Ducks
34.plot: Yuto wants to learn how to hit a baseball off a tee. / Oso teaches some kids how to play Duck, Duck, Goose.

35.title: The Sitter Who Watched Me/Potty Royale
35.plot: Oso helps Faith learn how to be comfortable staying with a babysitter. / Carson wants to go to preschool like his big brother, but first he needs to be able to use the potty by himself.

36.plot: When an experiment goes awry, Oso, Dotty and Wolfie are shrunk into miniature size. Oso must figure out how to rescue Wolfie and Dotty before time runs out and they all stay small forever.

1.title: To Grandma with Love/Gold Flower
1.plot: Oso gets a special assignment while learning how to walk in outer space. He must help a girl, Molly, plant marigold flowers in her garden. Will they complete the assignment before Molly's mother comes home from the store?

2.title: Never Say No Brushing Again/The Girl with the Golden Book
2.plot: Special Agent Oso's Special Assignment is to help Danny brush his teeth. / Special Agent Oso must help Samantha put the ripped page from her book back together so that mom can read her a story.

3.title: Live and Jump Rope/A View to a Kitten
3.plot: Abby doesn't know how to jump rope! So Special Agent Oso helps Abby learn the basics of rope jumping. / Special Agent Oso's Special Assignment is to help Aaron take a picture of his kitten for Grandpa.

4.title: View to a Book/Diamonds Are for Kites
4.plot: View To a Book: Oso gets a special assignment help a boy named Joe check out a library book about dinosaurs Diamonds Are for Kites: Oso gets a new special assignment to help Sarah (voice of Ciara) go kite flying in the park on kite day but soon discovers there isn't enough wind to fly kites. Oso has to use his special skills to save the day. Sarah helps Oso tie a knot in the string for the kite. That helps him cross the ravine and raise the green flag to earn his ravine crossing award.

5.title: The Boy with the Golden Gift/Birthdays Are Forever
5.plot: Special Agent Oso's Special Assignment: Help Michael wrap Quinn's birthday present. / Special Agent Oso must help Quinn make a party hat for his birthday photo.

6.title: Carousel Royale/Leaf Raker
6.plot: Oso must help Cassie find her ticket and ride the Carousel. / Special Agent Oso's Special Assignment to help Dawson rake up the leaves in his side yard.

7.title: Thunder Berries/Flowers Are Forever
7.plot: Special Agent Oso's Special Assignment must help Grace pick strawberries for her family's lunch. / Oso must help Caroline collect the wildflowers and press them in a book.

8.title: For Your Nice Bunny/For Pancakes with Love
8.plot: Oso's Special Assignment is to help Jim and Mia get their pet bunny's cage ready for Show and Tell. / Special Agent Oso must help Olivia make pancake batter.

9.title: License to Clean/On Her Cousin's Special Salad
9.plot: When Jake can't find one of his soccer shoes in his cluttered room, Special Agent Oso must help him sort out the messy problem. / When Jade is faced with making a salad, Special Agent Oso gets an alert.

10.title: Hide Another Day/Live and Let Dry
10.plot: Special Agent Oso must teach David how to play Hide and Seek. / Special Agent Oso helps Logan wash his breakfast dishes before he leaves for school.

11.title: License to Dress/Dr. Off
11.plot: Special Agent Oso must help Addison and her family save water and power. / Special Agent Oso's Special Assignment is to help Frank get dressed for school all by himself.

12.title: Octo-Puzzle/One Suitcase Is Now Enough
12.plot: Special Agent Oso's Special Assignment is to help Jack put his puzzle together to surprise his Dad. / Special Agent Oso must help Cody pack his suitcase for a family beach vacation.

13.title: Three Wheels Are Not Enough/A Zoo to a Thrill
13.plot: Special Agent Oso must help Paulie fix his wagon and deliver party supplies. / Oso's Special Assignment is to help Joon Kim feed a llama before the County Fair closes.

14.title: The Girl Who Cheered Me/A License to Twirl
14.plot: Special Agent Oso must help Maria learn the team cheer. / Oso's Special Assignment is to show Ava how to twirl a hoop around her waist.

15.title: For Show and Tell Only/Piggy Bank Royale
15.plot: Oso's Special Assignment is to help Grayson get ready for Show and Tell. / Special Agent Oso must help Michele fix her brother's broken piggy bank.

16.title: Hopscotch Royale/Goldringer
16.plot: Oso's Special Assignment is to help John and Alexis learn to play hopscotch. / Special Agent Oso must teach Chloe how to play horseshoes.

17.title: The Living Flashlight/Sand Castle Royale
17.plot: Oso's Special Assignment is to help Theo and Oliver get their flashlight to work before it gets dark. / Special Agent Oso must help Katie build a sand castle to surprise her mom.

18.title: License to Chill/GoldenFly
18.plot: Oso's Special Assignment is to help Tyler make frozen juice pops for his sister to take with her medicine. / Special Agent Oso's assignment is to help William catch a firefly before bedtime.

19.title: Tie Another Day/You Only Start PreSchool Once
19.plot: Oso must help Tara tie her new lace up shoes so she can wear them to school! / Oso special assignment is to help Sam make a friend before the class goes on a nature walk.

20.title: Goldfeather/Live and Let Ride
20.plot: Oso helps Brianna make a pinecone birdfeeder and hang it in a tree! / When Emma and her Dad need help finding the school bus stop, Special Agent Oso takes a break from his Rocket Launch Training Exercise to help.

21.title: For Your Pies Only/The Plates Are Not Enough
21.plot: Osorio is asked to help a boy buy sugar butter and 6 apples for a pie.

22.title: For Your Ice Only/Coldfingers
22.plot: Oso's Special Assignment is to help Carina learn to ice skate. / Oso helps Christopher and Ashley make a snowman before they have to go inside.

23.title: Nobody Draws It Better/Thunderbubble
23.plot: Oso helps Anna make her Daddy a new Valentine's Day card before he wakes up! / Oso's special assignment is to show Andrew how to blow bubbles for his grandparents' anniversary dance.

24.title: Recycling Is Forever/Goldswinger
24.plot: Oso helps Joshua recycle his family's bottles, cans and paper. / Oso's special assignment is to teach Natalie how to swing by herself.
